data.meta_description: Hôtel Tassel, designed by the renowned Belgian Art Nouveau architect Victor Horta, is a significant landmark in architectural history. Completed in 1893, it is considered his first mature Art Nouveau structure and has had a profound influence on the development of decorative style and free forms in architecture. The building's audacious bow-window and remarkable light wells have left a lasting mark on architectural history.
